    <p>The process for installing the memphis or sacramento deployment requires several JSON files
            that will be used when deploying the lifecycle manager.</p>
<section id="sample-node-provisionjson-file">
  <p>The following represents a sample <codeph>environment.json</codeph> file in the
                    <codeph>/var/hlm/clouds/&lt;cloudname&gt;</codeph> directory of the lifecycle
                manager for an unbonded NIC installation. The IP addresses are masked for security
                purposes. Use values appropriate for your environment.</p>
        
<codeblock>{
    "product": {
        "version": 1
    },

    "node-type": [
        {
            "name": "CCN",
            "interface-map": [
                {
                    "name": "INTF0",
                    "ethernet-port-map": {
                        "interface-ports": [ "eth0" ]
                    },
                    "logical-network-map": [
                        {
                            "name": "management",
                            "type": "vlan",
                            "segment-id": "203",
                            "network-address": {
                                "cidr": "10.20.3.0/24",
                                "start-address": "10.20.3.120",
                                "gateway": "10.20.3.1"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "api",
                            "type": "vlan",
                            "segment-id": "204",
                            "network-address": {
                                "cidr": "10.20.4.0/24",
                                "start-address": "10.20.4.120"
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "blockstore",
                            "type": "vlan",
                            "segment-id": "73",
                            "network-address": {
                                "cidr": "172.16.73.0/24",
                                "start-address": "172.16.73.120"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "DCN",
            "interface-map": [
                {
                    "name": "INTF0",
                    "ethernet-port-map": {
                        "interface-ports": [ "eth0" ]
                    },
                    "logical-network-map": [
                        {
                            "name": "management",
                            "ref": "ccn-INTF0-management"
                        },
                        {
                            "name": "datacenter",
                            "type": "vlan",
                            "segment-id": "205",
                            "network-address": {
                                "cidr": "10.20.5.0/24",
                                "start-address": "10.20.5.120",
                                "gateway": "10.20.5.1"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "INTF1",
                    "ethernet-port-map": {
                        "interface-ports": [ "eth1" ]
                   },
                    "logical-network-map": [
                        {
                            "name": "tenant",
                            "type": "vlan",
                            "segment-id": "",
                            "network-address": {
                                "cidr": "10.20.6.0/24",
                                "start-address": "10.20.6.120",
                                "gateway": "10.20.6.1"
                            }

                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "VRG",
            "interface-map": [
                {
                    "name": "INTF0",
                    "ethernet-port-map": {
                        "interface-ports": [ "eth0" ]
                    },
                    "logical-network-map": [
                        {
                            "name": "management",
                            "ref": "ccn-INTF0-management"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "INTF1",
                    "ethernet-port-map": {
                        "interface-ports": [ "eth1" ]
                    },
                    "logical-network-map": [
                       {
                            "name": "tenant",
                            "ref": "dcn-INTF1-tenant"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}</codeblock>
    
    
    <p> NOTE: The configuration processor assigns the first address of the CLM address range to itself for serving python 
        and debian repositories. Make sure that you set the first IP address of the CLM range for the eth2 (CLM) address of the KVM Host.</p>
            <p>Return to installing the non-KVM region for the:<ul id="ul_wnl_v4f_b5">
                    <li><xref href="CGH-2-install-tahoe.dita#topic10581c2it/env">Tahoe
                            deployment</xref></li>
                <li><xref href="CGH-2-install-memphis.dita#topic10581c2im/env">Memphis
                            deployment</xref></li>
                </ul></p>
    
        </section>
